## 🎓 Key Learnings & Technical Patterns

### 1. Unity-Specific Conventions

**Singleton Pattern (Correct Implementation):**
```csharp
void Awake()
{
    if (Instance != null && Instance != this)
    {
        Destroy(gameObject); // CRITICAL: Destroy entire GameObject, not just this component
        return;
    }
    Instance = this;
}
```
**Learning:** `Destroy(this)` leaves zombie GameObjects. Always `Destroy(gameObject)`.

**DontDestroyOnLoad Memory Management:**
```csharp
// WRONG: Creates duplicates on scene reload
GameObject vfxObj = Instantiate(prefab);
DontDestroyOnLoad(vfxObj);

// CORRECT: Reuse existing instances
wateringVFX = FindObjectOfType<WateringVFX>();
if (wateringVFX == null && wateringVFXPrefab != null)
{
    GameObject vfxObj = Instantiate(wateringVFXPrefab.gameObject);
    vfxObj.name = "WateringVFX_Instance"; // Named for debugging
    wateringVFX = vfxObj.GetComponent<WateringVFX>();
    DontDestroyOnLoad(vfxObj);
}
```

### 2. Defensive Programming (Critical!)

**Always Guard Array Access:**
```csharp
// WRONG:
float stageTime = cropData.growthTimePerStage[currentStage];

// CORRECT:
if (cropData.growthTimePerStage == null)
{
    Debug.LogError($"Array is null for {cropData.displayName}", this);
    return;
}

if (currentStage >= cropData.growthTimePerStage.Length)
{
    Debug.LogError($"Index {currentStage} out of bounds (length: {cropData.growthTimePerStage.Length})", this);
    return;
}

float stageTime = cropData.growthTimePerStage[currentStage];
```

**Null Checks Before Manager Calls:**
```csharp
if (GridManager.Instance == null)
{
    Debug.LogError("[System] GridManager not found!", this);
    return;
}
```

### 3. Order of Operations Matters

**Crop Instantiation Sequence (CRITICAL ORDER):**
```csharp
// 1. Validate FIRST (fail fast)
if (!GridManager.Instance.IsPositionAvailable(gridPos))
{
    Debug.LogWarning("Cell occupied");
    return false;
}

// 2. Create GameObject AFTER validation
GameObject cropObj = Instantiate(cropPrefab);

// 3. Set data BEFORE position (critical for Start() timing)
crop.SetCropData(cropData);
crop.SetGridPosition(gridPos);

// 4. Set position (may trigger Start())
cropObj.transform.position = worldPos;

// 5. Occupy cell AFTER setup complete
GridManager.Instance.TryOccupyCell(gridPos, cropObj);

// 6. Register
activeCrops[gridPos] = crop;
```

**Learning:** Setting `transform.position` can trigger Unity lifecycle methods (Start, OnEnable). Always set data BEFORE positioning.

### 4. VFX Integration Pattern

**Proper VFX Setup:**
1. Create prefab with VFX component
2. Parent instantiates and holds reference
3. Call `PlayAtPosition(Vector3)` for one-shot effects
4. Call `StartGlow()` / `StopGlow()` for persistent effects
5. Always scale VFX to match grid: `transform.localScale = Vector3.one * 0.03f` (for PPU 32, 680-800px sprites)

### 5. Data Validation (ScriptableObjects)

**OnValidate() Pattern:**
```csharp
void OnValidate()
{
    // Auto-correct invalid values
    for (int i = 0; i < growthTimePerStage.Length; i++)
    {
        if (growthTimePerStage[i] <= 0)
        {
            Debug.LogWarning($"Stage {i} time must be > 0, setting to 1.0");
            growthTimePerStage[i] = 1.0f;
        }
    }
    
    if (harvestQuantity <= 0)
    {
        Debug.LogWarning("Harvest quantity must be > 0, setting to 1");
        harvestQuantity = 1;
    }
}
```

